subSubSection.paragraph:
Prostomium semicircular with four red eyes, anterior eyes about 8× larger than posteriors (
Fig. 7C
). Median antenna inserted anterior to caruncle (
1.7 mm
long), longer than lateral antennae (
1 mm
). Anterior prostomial area blackish. Palps located laterally on buccal lips, as long as antennae (
1 mm
). Mouth ventral on chaetiger 2.

Parapodia biramous, notopodia with cirriform branchiae along first three chaetigers, longer than dorsal cirri. Second ventral cirri (
4.5 mm
) more than 3× longer than contiguous ones (
1 to 1.2 mm
).

All chaetae furcates, proportion between chaetae tines 1:4–1:5. Neurochaetae include long and short chaetae (
Fig. 7D, E
). Notochaetae longer and wider than neurochaetae (
Fig. 7F, G
).

Anus dorsal; pygidium with digitate anal cirri (
Fig. 7I
).
